      <!-- "Why is it different" section
      =================================== -->
      <div id="whyisitdifferent" class="row-fluid pitch">
        <div class="span5 offset1 justify">
          <div class="alert alert-success whyisdifferent">
            <p><strong>Why would I want another web travel-oriented service?</strong> You're already using <em>Foursquare</em>, <em>Tripadvisor</em>, <em>Virtualtourist</em> and many others. These services are great and <em>TellMeCicero</em> is not trying to compete with them. Therefore, you'll likely want to use <em>TellMeCicero</em> <strong>among</strong> the services that you're using now, <strong>not instead</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="alert alert-success">
            <p><strong>TellMeCicero is based upon a very simple idea</strong>: wherever the place you're in, it would be nice to hear stories that bring to the foreground the informations which no one knows about. So:
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">1</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Isn't about finding</strong> places (eg. <em>Foursquare</em>). <strong>Is about discovering</strong> something unexpected when in place.</div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">2</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Isn't about planning</strong> your travel (eg. <em>Virtualtourist</em>). <strong>Is about living</strong> your travel experience moment by moment.</div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">3</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Isn't about reviewing</strong> hotels or restaurants (eg. <em>Tripadvisor</em>). <strong>Is about conveying</strong> travel stories and personal feelings about things that haven't really seen the light of day.</div>
          </div>        
          <a href="#">Top</a>       
        </div>
        <div class="span5 video">
          <img class="img-polaroid" alt="Live your travel with local stories and advices" src="img/lUggXKg.jpg" title="Live your travel with local stories and advices">     
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- "How does it work" section
      =================================== -->
      <div id="howdoesitwork" class="row-fluid pitch">
        <div class="span5 offset1">
          <div class="alert alert-success howitworks justify">
            <p><em>TellMeCicero</em> is both a web site and an innovative mobile app to bring the whole travel experience to a new level. <em>TellMeCicero</em> app provides <strong>augmented reality</strong> features and the infrastructure for people to <strong>"plant" in a location audio and text stories to be used by travelers and others</strong>. Unleash the power of augmented reality through three simple steps:
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">1</span>
            <h5>Check-in</h5><br>
            <div class="text">Turn on <strong>GPS services</strong> on your device (smartphone, tablet and, pretty soon, Google Glass), launch <em>TellMeCicero app</em> and sign in.</div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">2</span>
            <h5>Point and discover</h5><br>
            <div class="text">Point your device around you and check for icons and graphic elements overlaying the screen.</div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">3</span>
            <h5>Get stories and advices</h5><br>
            <div class="text">Get along the way available audio and text stories provided by other travelers and locals, simply grabbing them from the screen.</div>
          </div>
          <a href="#">Top</a>       
        </div>
        <div class="span5 video">
          <img class="img-polaroid" alt="check-in, point and discover, get stories and advices" src="img/KYNb4Lm.jpg" title="Check-in, Point and Discover, Get Stories...">
  <!--        <img class="img-polaroid" alt="Memento Travel Journal - Design by Natalie Uhing (http://www.smallestforest.net) " src="http://i.imgur.com/mM9O4XV.jpg" title="The reward for premium supporters. A Memento Travel Journal designed by Natalie Uhing (http://www.smallestforest.net)"> -->
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- "Who are you" - traveler section
      =================================== -->
      <div id="whoareyou" class="row-fluid pitch">
        <div class="span5 offset1">
          <div class="alert alert-success whoareyou justify">
            <p><strong>As a traveler</strong>, we know that you want to experience the present moment of your travel. So you can:</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">1</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Record an audio story</strong> through <em>TellMeCicero app</em> and plant it in the place you're in by uploading to the <em>TellMeCicero cloud</em>. You can ask for an automatic text translation of your records via <em>speech-to-text</em> feature provided by <em>TellMeCicero platform</em>. </div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">2</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Share your stories and feelings about places</strong>, giving a valuable contribution to other travelers</div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">3</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Organize your multimedia travel memories</strong> (audio, post, pictures) through <em>TellMeCicero web site</em>, to compose your personal <strong>"memento travel journal"</strong></div>
          </div>        
        </div>
        <div class="span5 video">
          <img class="img-polaroid" alt="Memento Travel Journal - Design by Natalie Uhing (http://www.smallestforest.net) " src="img/mM9O4XV.jpg" title="The reward for premium supporters. An 'Analogic Memento Travel Journal' designed by Natalie Uhing (http://www.smallestforest.net)">
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- "Who are you" - local section
      =================================== -->
      <div id="whoareyou" class="row-fluid pitch">
        <div class="span5 offset1">
          <div class="alert alert-success justify">
            <p><strong>As a local</strong>, we know that you are the best Cicero of your area. So you can:</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">1</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Record and post stories about your birthplace</strong> or the place where you live.</div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">2</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Build alternative travel patterns about your place</strong>, organizing your contributions through <em>TellMeCicero web site</em>.</div>
          </div>        
          <div class="step textspace">
            <span class="badge badge-success">3</span>
            <div class="text inline"><strong>Share 'em all</strong> and make available to other people.</div>
          </div>        
          <a href="#">Top</a>       
        </div>
        <div class="span5 video">
          <img class="img-polaroid" alt="Rock church at the bottom of the Matera canyon" src="img/ooIzjut.jpg" title="This medieval rock church at the bottom of a canyon in Matera, Italy, is outside from the classical touristic routes and could be explained well only by local people">
        </div>
      </div>


